
void TOH(int n, char A, char B, char C){
    if(n == 1){
          print("Move 1 fromm " + A + "to " + C);
          return;
    }

    TOH(n-1,A,C,B);
    print("Move " + n + "from " + A + " to " + C);
    TOH(n-1,B,A,C);
}

_______________________________________________________

TOH(2, A, B, C)
      │
      ├── TOH(1, A, C, B)
      │   ├── TOH(0, A, B, C)
      │   ├── Move disk 1 from A → B
      │   └── TOH(0, C, A, B)
      │
      ├── Move disk 2 from A → C
      │
      └── TOH(1, B, A, C)
          ├── TOH(0, B, C, A)
          ├── Move disk 1 from B → C
          └── TOH(0, A, B, C)      

--------------------------------------------------

TOH(3, A, B, C)
│
├── TOH(2, A, C, B)
│   │
│   ├── TOH(1, A, B, C)
│   │   ├── TOH(0, A, C, B)
│   │   ├── Move disk 1 from A → C
│   │   └── TOH(0, B, A, C)
│   │
│   ├── Move disk 2 from A → B
│   │
│   └── TOH(1, C, A, B)
│       ├── TOH(0, C, B, A)
│       ├── Move disk 1 from C → B
│       └── TOH(0, A, C, B)
│
├── Move disk 3 from A → C
│
└── TOH(2, B, A, C)
    │
    ├── TOH(1, B, C, A)
    │   ├── TOH(0, B, A, C)
    │   ├── Move disk 1 from B → A
    │   └── TOH(0, C, B, A)
    │
    ├── Move disk 2 from B → C
    │
    └── TOH(1, A, B, C)
        ├── TOH(0, A, C, B)
        ├── Move disk 1 from A → C
        └── TOH(0, B, A, C)

////////////////////////////////////////////////////

TOH(n, A, B, C)
    |--> TOH(n-1, A, C, B)
    |--> Move Disc n from A to C
    |--> TOH(n-1, B, A, C)

# Tower of Hanoi: 3-Disk Visual Solution

This diagram illustrates the backtracking recursive steps to move 3 disks from **Peg A** to **Peg C**.

### Legend
- `████` : Disk 1 (Small)
- `████████` : Disk 2 (Medium)
- `████████████` : Disk 3 (Large)

